project-future-plans: Along with this challenge we are in discussions with several major payers to present the business case for identifying undiagnosed diabetes. Additionally, we are gathering letters of support for a National Science Foundation grant to fund a larger development of the project that pilot's an integration with an EHR system where the data can be pulled automatically.
project-inspiration: Everyone talks about the issues in healthcare with the rising costs and complexity where it is presented as this unsolvable problem. We started to look at the major causes of death in the United States and began to focus on diabetes. When we started getting into the statistics the numbers were startling - 86 million Americans are pre-diabetic and 9/10 of them do not know.  Approximately 28 million Americans are diabetic and 1/3 of them are unaware. At SEER Diagnostics we believe increasing awareness and education will help combat diabetes.
project-subtitle: Identifying care-gaps in undiagnoses diabetes to encourage treatment plans
